1. Definitions

    "Work": The creative work offered under this License, including but not limited to literary, software, artistic works, and any other copyrightable material.

    "Licensor": The individual or entity that offers the Work under the terms of this License.

    "Original Author": The Fineas AI core team members.

    "You": Any individual or legal entity exercising rights under this License.

    "Adaptation": A work derived from the original Work, including modifications, translations, or other alterations.

    "Distribute": To make the Work available to the public by any means, including sale, rental, lending, or sharing.

    "Collective Work": A compilation in which the Work is included in unmodified form alongside other separate and independent works.

    "Commercial Use": Any use of the Work intended for commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

    "Worker-Owned Entity": A business entity that is owned and democratically controlled by its workers, who actively participate in the governance and decision-making processes. This includes entities that meet the following criteria:

        Ownership: A majority of the ownership shares or interests are held by the workers of the entity.

        Participatory Governance: Each worker-member has voting rights in decision-making processes.

        Profit Distribution: Profits are distributed among the worker-members based on their labor contribution or equally, rather than based on capital investment.

        Worker Participation: Worker-members actively participate in the management and operations of the entity.

        Legal Structure: The entity is organized under applicable laws recognizing worker cooperatives or similar structures, such as under the Massachusetts General Laws Chapter 157A for employee cooperative corporations.

    "Nonprofit Organization": An organization formed for purposes other than generating profit and in which no part of the organization's income is distributed to its members, directors, or officers.

    "Sole Proprietorship": A business owned and operated by a single individual, where there is no legal distinction between the owner and the business.

    "Publicly Perform": To perform or display the Work, or Adaptations thereof, directly or by means of any device or process, in a place open to the public or to transmit or otherwise communicate the Work to the public by any means.

2. Grant of Rights
2.1 Rights Granted

Subject to the terms and conditions of this License, the Licensor hereby grants You a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, perpetual license to:

    Reproduce the Work, either as-is or as part of a Collective Work.
    Create Adaptations of the Work.
    Distribute and Publicly Perform the Work, Adaptations, and Collective Works.

2.2 Conditions for Commercial Use

    By Worker-Owned Entities, Nonprofit Organizations, and Sole Proprietorships:

        These entities may use the Work for Commercial Use without paying royalties, provided that:

            Any Adaptations or modified versions are made available to the public under the same terms as this License.

            They clearly indicate any changes made to the original Work.

            They make any Adaptations publicly available within 27 days of distribution or public performance.

    By Other Entities:

        Entities that are not Worker-Owned Entities, Nonprofit Organizations, or Sole Proprietorships must obtain a separate commercial license from the Licensor for Commercial Use.

        Alternatively, they may use the Work for Commercial Use under this License by:

            Paying a royalty fee of 10% of net profits derived from the Work to the Licensor, unless another arrangement is agreed upon in writing.

            Providing the Licensor with access to financial records related to the Work upon request, to verify the accuracy of royalty payments.

