4. Audit Rights
4.1 Audit of Royalty Payments

    Entities obligated to pay royalties under Section 2.2 must maintain accurate financial records related to the Work.

    The Licensor has the right to audit these records to verify the accuracy of royalty payments.

    Audits:

        Require a minimum of 27 days' written notice to the entity.

        Must be performed during regular business hours and in a manner that minimizes disruption.

    If an audit reveals an underpayment of more than 5%, the entity must:

        Pay the shortfall within 27 days.

        Reimburse the Licensor for reasonable audit costs.

